userStories.description:
Warn users when they try to navigate away from the page with unsaved time entries.

In `apps/web/src/pages/TimePage.tsx`:

1. Use `beforeunload` event to show browser warning when `hasChanges` is true:
   ```tsx
   useEffect(() => {
     const handleBeforeUnload = (e: BeforeUnloadEvent) => {
       if (hasChanges) {
         e.preventDefault()
         e.returnValue = ''
       }
     }
     window.addEventListener('beforeunload', handleBeforeUnload)
     return () => window.removeEventListener('beforeunload', handleBeforeUnload)
   }, [hasChanges])
   ```
2. Use React Router's `useBlocker` or similar to intercept in-app navigation when `hasChanges` is true.
3. Show confirmation dialog: "Du har osparade ändringar. Vill du lämna sidan utan att spara?"
4. If user confirms, discard changes and navigate.
5. If user cancels, stay on page.
6. Warning appears regardless of whether action bar is currently visible or hidden - it depends on `hasChanges`, NOT `showActionBar`.

Run typecheck to confirm no errors. Verify in browser using dev-browser skill.
